('', 'Design and performance analysis of low profile miniaturized MSPAs for body centric wireless communication in ISM band', 'International Journal of Computer Information Systems and Industrial Management Applications ', '2017', '9', '153-161', '1076655170NA', '', 'Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering, JK Lakshmipat University, Jaipur, India; Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering, PSIT, Kanpur, India; Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering, Manipal University, Jaipur, India; Amity School of Applied Sciences, Amity University, Rajasthan, India', 'Body centric wireless communication is emerging and active area of research for many applications as identification, tracking, health care systems and radio frequency linked telemetry. In this paper, On-body performance and analysis of various wearable square shaped spiral cut MSPAs were investigated by measuring reflection coefficient, radiation pattern and impact of human body equivalent model. This antenna is covering the industrial, scientific and medical band (ISM 2.45 GHz) which can be used for wearable applications in field of health care and telemetry. In particular, the designing and analysis focused on the performance of a miniaturized square shaped spiral cut MSPA for body centric wireless communication. The characterization of proposed antenna is analyzed using numerical equivalent of three layered canonical model of skin, fat and tissue. For all types of wearable square shaped spiral cut MSPA the main parameter under study is reflection coefficient and the effect of novel double C structured square shaped spiral cut MSPA with miniaturized designs. Â© MIR Labs.', '', '', 'Machine Intelligence Research (MIR) Labs', '21507988', 'NA', '', '', 'Journal', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Design and verification of Ethernet, VME IP core using ACE and CDC', '2nd International Conference on Electronics and Communication Systems, ICECS 2015 ', '2015', '', '194-198', '10.1109/ECS.2015.7124891', '', 'Department of ECE, SEEC, Manipal University Jaipur(MUJ), Jaipur, India; Department of ECE, NEHU, Shillong, India; CMRTC, Hyderabad, India; CVC Pvt Ltd, Bangalore, India', 'In todays verification field System-On-a-Chip (SOC) designs contain increased levels of functional and structural complexities. Different SOCs having various design blocks and those blocks are operated at different clock frequencies which causes CDC issues. The CDC issues are visualized through ACE using Blue Pearl Software Suite. In this paper we discuss about Advance Clock Environment (ACE) and Clock Domain Crossing (CDC) using Blue Pearl Software Suite (BPS) of Ethernet and VME(Voice Modulation Engine) IP Core. Â© 2015 IEEE.', '', '', 'Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc.', 'NA', '9781479972241', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Design of a novel compact planar monopole UWB antenna with triple band-notched characteristics', '2nd International Conference on Signal Processing and Integrated Networks, SPIN 2015 ', '2015', '', '56-59', '10.1109/SPIN.2015.7095346', '', 'Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering, Manipal University, Jaipur, India; Department of Mechatronics, Manipal University, Jaipur, India', 'In this paper a compact planar UWB antenna with triple band-notched characteristics has been presented. The design consists of a unique lamp post shaped radiator fed through a microstrip feedline with a pair of etched U-shaped slots and a C-shaped slot. The proposed antenna has been successfully simulated using CST MWS Suite. The proposed antenna of size 30 Ã— 30mm2 is very compact and easy to integrate with hand held devices. The antenna reports a large bandwidth from 2.68 GHz to 10.65 GHz with VSWR â‰¤ 2 over the entire range except at three notched bands for WiMax systems at 3.3-3.7 GHz, WLAN systems at 5.15-5.85 GHz and 7.25-8.40 GHz for uplink and downlink of X-band satellite communication systems. The proposed antenna exhibits nearly omni-directional radiation pattern and a stable gain over the entire impedance bandwidth except for the three notched bands. Â© 2015 IEEE.', '', '', 'Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc.', 'NA', '9781479959914', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Design of a robust receiver for chaotic switching maps of DC-DC power electronics transmitter converters for secure communication', 'Security and Communication Networks ', '2016', '9', '4403-4415', '10.1002/sec.1616', '', 'Electrical and Electronics Engineering Department, Manipal University Jaipur, Jaipur, Rajasthan, India; Electrical and Electronics Engineering Department, Sikkim Manipal Institute of Technology, Gangtok, Sikkim, India; Pro President, Manipal University Jaipur, Jaipur, Rajasthan, India', 'This paper aims to open a new vista of research in the direction of possible application of power electronics DC-DC converters in analog chaotic communication. Most of the work reported on analog chaotic communication is based on the pioneer work of Pecora and Caroll, with synchronization between transmitter and receiver. Receiver based on synchronization, also known as coherent receiver, has a disadvantage of parameter mismatch and is sensitive to noise. In the present work, firstly, a secure transmitter using chaotic DC-DC converters is proposed that encrypts information using chaotic switching map technique. In chaotic switching map technique, the message is encrypted by randomly switching from one chaotic converter to another. The bifurcation parameter of the randomly switched chaotic converter is modulated by the message. Secondly, an attempt has been made to design a robust non-coherent receiver that is adaptable to the switching chaotic transmitters, even in the presence of noise. Once the receiver identifies the chaotic converter, it can decode the message as per the decryption algorithm. With the proposed non-coherent receiver, the disadvantages of coherent receivers can be overcome. We have also devised a prototype smart meter, used in smart distribution grid for implementing the proposed communication technique. Copyright Â© 2016 John Wiley & Sons, Ltd. Copyright Â© 2016 John Wiley & Sons, Ltd.', '', '', 'John Wiley and Sons Inc.', '19390114', 'NA', '', '', 'Journal', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Design of a triple band-notched UWB planar monopole antenna', 'Journal of Microwaves, Optoelectronics and Electromagnetic Applications ', '2015', '14', '184-196', '10.1590/2179-10742015v14i2514', '', 'Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering, Manipal University, Jaipur, India', 'In this paper, a novel design of a compact planar ultra wide band (UWB) monopole antenna with triple band notched characteristics has been presented. The antenna has a unique shape and has been fed through a 50 Ï‰ microstrip feedline. The strength of the antenna lies in three band notched properties for WiMax system at 3.3-3.7 GHz, WLAN IEEE 802.11a at 5.15-5.85 GHz and X band satellite communication at 7.25-8.395 GHz. The notched bands have been achieved by incorporating an inverted U-slot etched on the radiator patch, an inverted C-slot also on the radiator patch and a U-slot on the microstrip feed line. In order to achieve FCC defined impedance bandwidth of 7.5 GHz, a rectangular cut in the ground plane has been introduced along with staircase structure in the bottom edge of the radiator. The proposed antenna is having a compact size of 30 X 30 X 1.6 mm3 and exhibits a large bandwidth from 2.8 GHz to 10.7 GHz. The antenna has been successfully simulated and fabricated. The radiation pattern is omni-directional in H-plane and the E-plane exhibits dipole like radiation pattern. The gain of the antenna is stable across the whole operating frequency band except at three notched bands. Â© 2015 SBMO/SBMag.', '', '', 'Sociedade Brasileira de Microondas e Optoeletronica (SBMO)', '21791074', 'NA', '', '', 'Journal', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Design of channel ADD Drop filter using photonic crystal ring resonator', '2017 International Conference on Computer, Communications and Electronics, COMPTELIX 2017 ', '2017', '', '124-129', '10.1109/COMPTELIX.2017.8003950', '', 'Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering, Manipal University, Jaipur, India; Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering, MNIT, Jaipur, India', 'In this paper various design of channel ADD Drop filter using photonic crystal ring resonator is investigated. In design I, ADF based on quasi-square PCRR with circular scatters is proposed and analysed for optimized performance. This device consists of rectangular waveguides and a quasi-square PCRR. A good wavelength selective filter with bandwidth about 10.20nm and centre wavelength of pass band 1.4201um is achieved. In the next design, photonic crystal quasi-square cavity based ADF is realised with elliptical scatters for different major and minor axis configurations thus having different ellipticity. It is observed that the output response of the filter is very sensitive to the dimensions of coupling rods and scatter rods. It is observed that when the radius of the scatter rods is increased, then the centre wavelength of the bands get shifted towards higher wavelength range. Â© 2017 IEEE.', '', '', 'Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc.', 'NA', '9781509047086', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Design of circularly polarized planar magneto-electric dipole Antenna', 'Progress In Electromagnetics Research C ', '2016', '67', '21-29', '10.2528/PIERC16062306', '', 'Department of Electronics and Communication, Manipal University Jaipur, Jaipur, India; Department of Electronics and Communication, Maharaja Agrasen Institute of Technology, Delhi, India', 'A new design of a circularly polarized planar magneto-electric dipole antenna is proposed and presented. This antenna consists of dual horizontal T-shaped electric dipole and an inverted Ushaped feed line. The antenna possesses 21.1% impedance bandwidth, from 8.9 GHz-11.0GHz, provides 3-dB axial ratio bandwidth of 9.52% ranging 10.0GHz-11.0GHz, exhibits stable omnidirectional radiation pattern with almost equal E-plane and H-plane radiation patterns and provides a peak gain of 6.2 dBi. Due to its good electrical characteristics and radiation parameters, the antenna is suitable for satellite and RADAR communication in X-band. Â© 2016, Electromagnetics Academy. All rights reserved.', '', '', 'Electromagnetics Academy', '19378718', 'NA', '', '', 'Journal', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Design of CPW fed printed slot antenna with circular polarization for UWB application', 'AIP Conference Proceedings ', '2016', '1715', '', '10.1063/1.4942713', '', 'Microwave Lab, Department of Physics, University of Rajasthan, Jaipur, India; Department of Physics, Manipal University, Jaipur, India', 'This paper reports the design and performance of a CPW-fed circularized polarized elliptical slot antenna for UWB (ultra wide band) applications. The circular polarization is achieved by applying triangular stubs in the ground plane. The overall volume of this antenna is 40mm Ã— 40mm Ã— 1.59mm. The proposed antenna is simulated by applying CST Microwave Studio simulator. This elliptical patch slot antenna provides broad impedance bandwidth (3.1GHz to 10.6 GHz) with maximum gain 4.31dB at 4.45GHz. The simulated 3-dB axial ratio bandwidth is close to 2.51GHz (from 4.76GHz to 7.27GHz) which is 41.76% with respect to the central frequency 6.01GHz. Â© 2016 AIP Publishing LLC.', '', '', 'American Institute of Physics Inc.', '0094243X', '9780735413627', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Design of hybrid photonic crystal fiber with elliptical and circular air holes analyzed for large flattened dispersion and high birefringence', 'Journal of Nanophotonics ', '2016', '10', '', '10.1117/1.JNP.10.026016', '', 'Manipal University Jaipur, Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering, Rajasthan, India; Malaviya National Institute of Technology Jaipur, Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering, Rajasthan, India', 'A design of two-dimensional hybrid photonic crystal fiber (PCF) with elliptical and circular air holes and its analyses for large flattened dispersion and high birefringence is presented. The PCF has hexagonal layout with triangular lattice. There are five rings around the solid core. The inner three rings around the core have elliptical air holes while the outer two rings have circular air holes. Three such layouts are designed, analyzed, and compared with the layout having only circular air hole using full-vector finite difference time domain method. The layout with hybrid structure having combined elliptical and circular air hole gives a large flattened dispersion of the order of 4.88 ps/nm/km for the wavelength range of 1.2 to 1.8 Î¼m and magnitude of modal birefringence is 1.238 Ã— 10-3 at 1.55-Î¼m wavelength. Â© 2016 Society of Photo-Optical Instrumentation Engineers (SPIE).', '', '', 'SPIE', '19342608', 'NA', '', '', 'Journal', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Design of octagonal and decagonal lattice photonic crystal fiber for achieving ultra low flattened dispersion', 'Lecture Notes in Electrical Engineering ', '2018', '472', '39-49', '10.1007/978-981-10-7395-3_5', '', 'Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering, Malaviya National Institute of Technology Jaipur, Jaipur, Rajasthan, India; Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering, Manipal University Jaipur, Jaipur, Rajasthan, India; Department of Mathematics, Malaviya National Institute of Technology Jaipur, Jaipur, Rajasthan, India', 'This paper presents some key concepts of design and optimization of solid core photonic crystal fiber (PCF) based on different geometries for broadband applications. The three different geometrical structures, hexagonal, octagonal, and decagonal of photonic crystal fiber, are designed for different air filling fractions at pitch length 2 Î¼m. The parameters affecting the light propagation through PCF structure such as effective refractive index, chromatic dispersion, mode effective area, nonlinear coefficient, and V parameter are numerically analyzed and compared using finite element method (FEM) on COMSOL Multiphysics software. Â© 2018, Springer Nature Singapore Pte Ltd.', '', '', 'Springer Verlag', '18761100', '9789811073946', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Design of planar monopole UWB antenna with modified slotted-patch', 'Journal of Advanced Research in Dynamical and Control Systems ', '2018', '10', '63-69', '478255223NA', '', 'Dept. of EEE, BITS Pilani, Goa Campus, India; Amity UniversityRajasthan, India; Manipal University, Jaipur, India; Department of EEE, BITS PilaniGoa, India', 'An ultra-wideband antenna (UWB) is presented in this paper, having the properties of small size and high return loss. Simulations and measurements show that the antenna which is designed in this paper has nearly omnidirectional radiation patterns on the transmission band and achieves a good gain, which enables it to be used for different UWB applications. It is designed using FR-4 (Lossy) substrate which is low cost and commercially available and the model is validated through extensive simulations performed in CST MWS 2014. The proposed design is achieved using 3 steps with each step resulting in a great enhancement in the bandwidth. The proposed antenna works for frequencies from 8 â€“ 17.6 GHz resulting in a huge bandwidth of 9.6 GHz. The proposed antenna provides this huge bandwidth with a minimal size of 24Ã—28 mm2. The results are evident that the proposed antenna can be used for all Ku-Band (12-18 GHz) and X-Band (8-12 GHz) applications including Radar and Satellite Communications and Weather Monitoring. Details about the gain, radiation efficiency, radiation pattern and surface current are being described in this paper. Â© 2018, Institute of Advanced Scientific Research, Inc. All rights reserved.', '', '', 'Institute of Advanced Scientific Research, Inc.', '1943023X', 'NA', '', '', 'Journal', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Design optimization of a highly birefringent and highly nonlinear silicon photonic crystal fiber', 'Lecture Notes in Electrical Engineering ', '2018', '472', '301-308', '10.1007/978-981-10-7395-3_34', '', 'Department of ECE, Malaviya National Institute of Technology, Jaipur, Rajasthan, India; Department of ECE, Manipal University, Jaipur, India', 'This paper presents an optimum design for highly birefringent and highly nonlinear photonic crystal fiber based on modified spiral photonic crystal fiber structure. The PCF structure includes an elliptical slot in the core of the fiber. The finite element method is used to investigate the guiding property. The simulation results show that nonlinear coefficient at 1.55 Î¼m wavelength for X and Y polarization is 2951 and 1379, respectively. This design also offers high birefringence up to 0.292219 at 1550 nm wavelength. In addition to this, confinement factor is also reported and discussed. Â© Springer Nature Singapore Pte Ltd. 2018.', '', '', 'Springer Verlag', '18761100', '9789811073946', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Design planar microstrip antenna for wireless and lower UWB applications using DGS', '2016 International Conference on Recent Advances and Innovations in Engineering, ICRAIE 2016 ', '2017', '', '', '10.1109/ICRAIE.2016.7939597', '', 'Department of Elec. and Comm., Poornima University, Jaipur, India; Department of Elec. and Comm., Manipal University, Jaipur, India', 'A new wideband compact planar microstrip antenna with defected ground structure is presented. The compact size of antenna is 57 mm Ã— 46 mm Ã— 1.59 mm. Defected ground structure antenna has minimum return loss of-24.77 dB and-19.04 dB at operating frequency 5.57 GHz and 3.51 GHz respectively. This antenna provides percentage bandwidth of 52%, ranging from 3.4 GHz to 5.9 GHz with constant gain. This antenna is useful structure for lower ultra wideband (UWB) applications along with modern wireless communication systems such as WI-FI, WLAN and Wi-Max bands. Â© 2016 IEEE.', '', '', 'Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc.', 'NA', '9781509028078', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Design process of a compact UWB slotted planar monopole antenna by introduction of slots', 'Journal of Advanced Research in Dynamical and Control Systems ', '2018', '10', '519-527', '1325852213NA', '', 'BITS, PILANI, Dept. of EEE, Goa Campus, India; Amity UniversityRajasthan, India; Manipal university, Jaipur, India; EEE & I, Bits Pilani, KK Birla Goa CampusGoa, India', 'The objective of this paper is to describe the technique of improvement of Ultra Wideband Antennas (UWB) and also how to design them. A simple design, a smaller structure and better return loss is expected from the antenna. The simulations show that that the antennas has a good amplification factor and a nearly omnidirectional properties in the proposed bandwidth region. The substrate used in the designing of this antenna is FR-4 (Lossy) which is a low cost substrate and the designs were simulated extensively using the CST MWS 2014. The progression in the design of this antenna is shown through three successive iterations which progressively further enhances the desired result The final bandwidth in the third iteration operates in the frequency range 3.28-20GHz resulting in a bandwidth of 16.72GHz. The size of the substrate used in this antennas is 25x30 mm2. The results show that the proposed antenna can operate in C Band (4 GHz to 8 GHz), X Band (8 GHz-12GHz) and Ku-Band (12 GHz to 18GHz). Multiple plots describing the gain, radiation efficiency, radiation pattern and surface current have been shown in this paper. Â© 2018, Institute of Advanced Scientific Research, Inc. All rights reserved.', '', '', 'Institute of Advanced Scientific Research, Inc.', '1943023X', 'NA', '', '', 'Journal', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Detection of infected and healthy part of leaf using image processing techniques', 'Journal of Advanced Research in Dynamical and Control Systems ', '2017', '9', '13-19', '1030611164NA', '', 'Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering, Manipal University, Jaipur, Rajasthan, India; Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering, K L University, Guntur (Dt.), Vaddeswaram, Andhra Pradesh, India; Plant Pathology, Rajasthan Agricultural Research Institute, Durgapura, Jaipur, Rajasthan, India', 'Plant disease is one of the major reasons that degrade the quantity and quality of agricultural products. Therefore, to detect and classify the plant disease at an early stage is a significant task for agriculture engineering. This paper proposes an algorithm to diagnosis the diseased leaf using Weiner filtering with different window size i.e. n=10, 20, 30 out of which n=20 gives better detection efficiency and adaptive histogram equalization is used to remove background noise. Different edge detection techniques were used to detect the edges of infected and healthy leaf parts in which canny gives 80-99% of accuracy. The present approach is used to analyze the diseased leaf at initial stage to initiate necessary precautions that can be taken in time to minimize the yield losses. Â© 2017, Institute of Advanced Scientific Research, Inc. All rights reserved.', '', '', 'Institute of Advanced Scientific Research, Inc.', '1943023X', 'NA', '', '', 'Journal', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Detection time of machine by posit algorithm through augmented reality', 'ICCT 2017 - International Conference on Intelligent Communication and Computational Techniques ', '2018', '2018-January', '71-78', '10.1109/INTELCCT.2017.8324023', '', 'Department of Computer Science, Manipal University, Jaipur, India', 'Augmented Reality is the combination of virtual scene generated from computer with the users real world. Nowadays, many applications apply augmented reality technology in defense sector, traffic management, which uses real time system, where time is an important factor. In this paper, an efficient augmented reality system is suggested to compute the response time of machine to detect the marker. Luminous affecting computing of glyph recognition and detection of glyph by marker at different challenging distance (feet) has been processed. Glyph is created for augmented process through image processing and glyph matrix representation has been structured. Here, Posit algorithm is used to detect the position and orientation of marker with respect to camera. A prototype structure is created to compute the detection response time of machine under different challenging conditions. Our experimental result shows minimum computation Detection time is 5400 millisecond at lux 13490 (ambient light) and maximum computation detection time is 12000 millisecond at Lux 10.3 (no tube-light) to detect the fiducial marker. Â© 2017 IEEE.', '', '', 'Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc.', 'NA', '9781538630303', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Determining the dimensions of organizational climate perceived by the hotel employees', 'Journal of Hospitality and Tourism Management ', '2018', '36', '40-48', '10.1016/j.jhtm.2018.07.001', '', 'School of Hotel Management, Manipal University Jaipur, VPO Dehmi Kalan, Jaipur-Ajmer Expressway, Jaipur, India; TAPMI School of Business, Manipal University Jaipur, VPO Dehmi Kalan, Jaipur-Ajmer Expressway, Jaipur, India', 'This study identifies the dimensions of organizational climate perceived by the hospitality employees and measures the perceptual differences among the employees about the organizational climate. Data were obtained from 504 employees across 18 luxury hotels in India. Exploratory factor analysis identified five components explaining 60.11% variance. However, confirmatory factor analysis revealed a more precise and validated four dimensional climate constructs labelled as â€˜Esprit of Profession, Organization & Workgroupâ€™; â€˜Leader Facilitation & Supportâ€™; â€˜Cohesion, Clarity & Objectivity of Systemâ€™ and â€˜Job Challenge, Variety & Feedbackâ€™. Analysis of variance determined that significant differences in perception exist among the employees of different star category of hotel, job positions and gender about the climate. This study contributes to the knowledge related to organizational climate in the field of hospitality and the findings would be useful for hotels in improving their organizational climate. Â© 2018', '', '', 'Elsevier Ltd', '14476770', 'NA', '', '', 'Journal', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Development of aluminum metal foam using blowing agent', 'IOP Conference Series: Materials Science and Engineering ', '2018', '377', '', '10.1088/1757-899X/377/1/012150', '', 'Department of Mechanical Engineering, Manipal University, Jaipur, India', 'This paper describes the complete manufacturing process for production of the aluminium foam with its achieved important physical properties and its uses in various industries. The production process of aluminum metallic foam includes high purity molten aluminium in which a small amount of calcium carbonate powder is continuously faded and stirred thoroughly. The decomposition of calcium carbonate release gases, which are entrapped in high viscous mixture of the molten aluminium and calcium residues and create low density porous aluminium foam as shown in figure no. 7 and figure no. 8. The aluminum foam is collected and cooled in the mold. Afterward foam is removed from the mold and cut to the desired sizes. The foam with low density 848 kg/m3 is obtained and density of which is 0.342 times of pure aluminum. Â© Published under licence by IOP Publishing Ltd.', '', '', 'Institute of Physics Publishing', '17578981', 'NA', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Development of system for controlling voltage Sags/Swells using dynamic voltage restorer', '2015 International Conference on Recent Developments in Control, Automation and Power Engineering, RDCAPE 2015 ', '2015', '', '172-176', '10.1109/RDCAPE.2015.7281390', '', 'Dept. of Electronics and Electrical Engineering, SEEC, Manipal University, Jaipur (MUJ), Jaipur, Rajasthan, India; Dept. of Electrical Engineering, DMIETR, Wardha, Maharashtra, India', 'Power Quality is one of the critical issues in the power distribution system operations, nowadays. Due to implementation of complex power device, their performance becomes very sensitive with the quality of power supply. This paper demonstrates the application of a dynamic voltage restorer to resolve the quality problems of the voltage Sags/Swells which may be severe for many sensitive loads. The proposed scheme is very simple to implement. The design and simulationsare carried out using MATLAB. Â© 2015 IEEE.', '', '', 'Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc.', 'NA', '9781479972470', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Diaminomaleonitrile based chromo-fluorescent receptor molecule for selective sensing of Mn(II) and Zn(II) ions', 'Sensors and Actuators, B: Chemical ', '2018', '260', '1012-1017', '10.1016/j.snb.2018.01.106', '', 'Department of Chemistry, Manipal University Jaipur, VPO- Dehmi-Kalan, Off Jaipur-Ajmer express way, Jaipur, Rajasthan, India', 'A new class of chemosensors (L1-L3) based on sequential coupling of 2,3-diaminomaleonitrile, 4-formyl-1-substituted phenyl-pyrazole-3-carboxylate and 2-hydroxy-1-naphthaldehyde through imine linkages were successfully designed and synthesized. The synthesized chemosensors showed quick colorimetric response with excellent selectivity and sensitivity towards detection of Mn2+ and Zn2+ ions in preference of other cations. Along with this, chemosensors also serve as fluorescent turn â€˜offâ€™ and turn â€˜onâ€™ switch for detection of Mn2+ and Zn2+ ion respectively. Analytical characterization were evaluated using UVâ€“vis titration, fluorescent titration and Jobs plot methods which revealed that sensor interact with Mn2+ and Zn2+ ion in 1:1 and 1:2 binding stoichiometry respectively. Â© 2018 Elsevier B.V.', '', '', 'Elsevier B.V.', '09254005', 'NA', '', '', 'Journal', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Differential search algorithm for multiobjective problems', 'Procedia Computer Science ', '2015', '48', '22-28', '10.1016/j.procs.2015.04.105', '', 'Computer Science and Engineering Department, Manipal University, Jaipur, Rajasthan, India; Computer Engineering Department, National Institute of Technology, Kurukshetra, Haryana, India; Computer Science and Engineering Department, GJUSandT, Hisar, Haryana, India', 'In this paper, a novel Differential Search Algorithm (DSA) approach is proposed to solve multiobjective optimization problems, called Multiobjective Differential Search Algorithm (MODSA). MODSA utilizes the concept of Pareto dominance to determine the direction of a super-organism and it maintains non-dominated solutions in the external repository. This approach also uses the external repository of super-organisms that is used to guide other super-organisms. It guides the artificial organisms to search towards non-crowding and external regions of Pareto front. The performance of proposed approach is evaluated against the other well-known multiobjective optimization algorithms over a set of multiobjective benchmark test functions. Experimental results reveal that the MODSA outperforms the other competitive algorithms for benchmark test functions. Â© 2015 The Authors. Published by Elsevier B.V.', '', '', 'Elsevier B.V.', '18770509', 'NA', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Discrimination of Satellite Signals from Opencast Mining of Mineral Ores of Hematite and Uranium Using Digital Image Processing and Geostatistical Algorithms', 'Advances in Intelligent Systems and Computing ', '2018', '723', '193-199', '10.1007/978-3-319-74690-6_19', '', 'Department of Remote Sensing, Birla Institute of Technology, Mesra, Ranchi, Jharkhand, India; Department of Computer Science and Engineering, Manipal University, Jaipur, Rajasthan, India', 'This study has been conducted on mining areas of Gua and Banduhurang in Jharkhand State, India, Barbil in Orissa State, India and Mines dâ€™Arlit, Niger. Data from the corresponding sensors of EO-I, LANDSAT and IRS (i.e., Hyperion, ETM+ and LISS III respectively) were used to discriminate satellite signals of Hematite and Uranium ores from these locations. For the data of Hyperion being hyper-spectral, correction mechanism were performed through relevant algorithms: Fast Line-of-sight Atmospheric Analysis of Hypercube (FLAASH) to remove atmospheric aerosol effects, Minimum Noise Fraction (MNF) to remove noise, Pixel Purity Index (PPI) to get spectrally the most pure pixel and Spectral Angle Mapper (SAM) in order to match the spectral similarity between an image pixel spectrum and a referenced spectrum. The data achieved from ETM+ had line-stripping, and thus were restored. On the LISS III data, vegetation had to be, virtually, removed from the images of the Indian sites, using Normalized Difference Vegetation Index (NDVI), in order to equate them with that from the Niger site. The processed data was put to a common platform statistically. Segregation of Uranium, a radioactive ore, from Hematite, a non-radioactive iron ore, could be achieved up to 82.35% using TOPSIS and 90% using pair-wise Studentâ€™s t-Test. The technique of Band Ratio was also carried out and an index was generated to isolate these mines from their surroundings. Â© 2018, Springer International Publishing AG.', '', '', 'Springer Verlag', '21945357', '9783319746890', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'DNA as an electromagnetic fractal cavity resonator: Its universal sensing and fractal antenna behavior', 'Advances in Intelligent Systems and Computing ', '2018', '584', '213-223', '10.1007/978-981-10-5699-4_21', '', 'Amity School of Applied Science, Amity University Rajasthan, Jaipur, Rajasthan, India; Visual Perception and Psychophysics Laboratory, School of Optometry, Universite de Montreal, Montreal, Canada; Manipal University, Jaipur, India; Natural Products Chemistry Division, CSIR-North East Institute of Science & Technology, Jorhat, Assam, India; Advanced Key Technologies Division, Advanced Nano Characterization Center, National Institute for Materials Science, 1-2-1 Sengen, Tsukuba, Japan', 'We report that 3D-A-DNA structure behaves as a fractal antenna, which can interact with the electromagnetic fields over a wide range of frequencies. Using the lattice details of human DNA, we have modeled radiation of DNA as a helical antenna. The DNA structure resonates with the electromagnetic waves at 34Â GHz, with a positive gain of 1.7Â dBi. We have also analyzed the role of three different lattice symmetries of DNA and the possibility of soliton-based energy transmission along the structure. Â© 2018, Springer Nature Singapore Pte Ltd.', '', '', 'Springer Verlag', '21945357', '9789811056987', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'DTM Simulation of Peristaltic Viscoelastic Biofluid Flow in Asymmetric Porous Media: A Digestive Transport Model', 'Journal of Bionic Engineering ', '2015', '12', '643-655', '10.1016/S1672-6529(14)60154-2', '', 'Department of Mechanical Engineering, Manipal University Jaipur, Jaipur, India; Gort Engovation-Bio-Propulsion Research, Gabriels Wing House, Bradford, United Kingdom; Department of Mathematics, National Institute of Technology Silchar, Silchar, India; Department of Mathematics, National Institute of Technology, Warangal, India; School of Electrical and Electronic Engineering, The University of Adelaide, Adelaide, SA, Australia', 'A biofluid dynamics mathematical model is developed to study peristaltic flow of non-Newtonian physiological liquid in a two-dimensional asymmetric channel containing porous media as a simulation of obstructed digestive (intestinal) transport. The fractional Oldroyd-B viscoelastic rheological model is utilized. The biophysical flow regime is constructed as a wave-like motion and porous medium is simulated with a modified Darcy-Brinkman model. This model is aimed at describing the digestive transport in intestinal tract containing deposits which induce impedance. A low Reynolds number approximation is employed to eliminate inertial effects and the wavelength to diameter ratio is assumed to be large. The differential transform method (DTM), a semi-computational technique is employed to obtain approximate analytical solutions to the boundary value problem. The influences of fractional (rheological material) parameters, relaxation time, retardation time, amplitude of the wave, and permeability parameter on peristaltic flow characteristics such as volumetric flow rate, pressure difference and wall friction force are computed. The present model is relevant to flow in diseased intestines. Â© 2015 Jilin University.', '', '', 'Science Press', '16726529', 'NA', '', '', 'Journal', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Dual output voltage differencing buffered amplifier based wave active filter', '2015 IEEE UP Section Conference on Electrical Computer and Electronics, UPCON 2015 ', '2016', '', '', '10.1109/UPCON.2015.7456736', '', 'Deptt. of Electronics and Communication Engg., Graphic Era Hill University, Dehradun, India; Deptt. of Mechatronics Engg., Manipal University, Jaipur, India; Deptt. of Electrical Engg., Delhi Technological University, New Delhi, India', 'In this paper, a wave active filter structure based on Voltage Differencing Buffered Amplifier (VDBA) is presented. The proposed structure uses a lower number of active building blocks for ladder simulation using grounded capacitors. The workability of the proposed structure is verified for a 4th order low pass Butterworth filter using PSPICE simulation with 0.18Î¼m TSMC CMOS technology parameters. Ã¯Â¿Â½ 2015 IEEE.', '', '', 'Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc.', 'NA', '9781467385077', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Dufour-soret and thermophoretic effects on magnetohydrodynamic mixed convection casson fluid flow over a moving wedge and non-uniform heat source/sink', 'International Journal of Fluid Mechanics Research ', '2018', '45', '51-74', '10.1615/InterJFluidMechRes.2018020450', '', 'Manipal University Jaipur, Jaipur, Rajasthan, India', 'The present work examined the computational study of Dufour-Soret and thermophoresis effects of magnetohydrodynamic (MHD) Casson fluid over a moving wedge with viscous dissipation, porous medium, and non-uniform heat source. The impact of wedge angle parameter and thermal buoyancy parameter was also included in this study. A similar transformation is applied to convert the non-linear partial differential equations into ordinary partial differential equations. For solving these equations we have used Runge-Kutta fourth-fifth-order Fehlberg Method (RKF-45) with shooting technique. The skin friction coefficient, Nusselt number, and Sherwood number are also analyzed. The results of various parameters are shown through graphically and in tabular form. Â© 2018 by Begell House, Inc.', '', '', 'Begell House Inc.', '10642277', 'NA', '', '', 'Journal', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Dynamic weighted virtual machine live migration mechanism to manages load balancing in cloud computing', '2016 IEEE International Conference on Computational Intelligence and Computing Research, ICCIC 2016 ', '2017', '', '', '10.1109/ICCIC.2016.7919581', '', 'Dept. of Computer Science and Engineering, Manipal University Jaipur, Jaipur, India', 'Load Balancing is a mechanism of efficient utilization of computing resources (i.e. CPU, Memory and Network). Cloud computing is the best option to reduce CAPEX and OPEX of the organizations. High Quality of Service (QoS) and reduction the Service Level Agreement (SLA) violation depend on efficient management of Load Imbalance problem. Cloud Service efficiency depends on proper management of physical and logical resources. Researchers did lots of work on the effective load management system. Researchers used many approaches (i.e. Ant colony, Honey Bee, Genetic, Static, and Dynamic) but still need improvement. Virtual Machines (VMs) migration system plays the vital role in load management. Our focus in this research is maximizing the utilization of VMs CPU capacity. Proposed research approach is based on Dynamic Weighted Live Migration (DWLM) to manage load imbalance problem. The proposed mechanism results outcomes compared with Migration time, Scalability, Throughput and Availability factor from Equally Spread Current Execution load balancing algorithm (ESCEL) and Push Pull algorithm. This paper also focuses on others load balancing strategies and future research scope in Load management mechanism. Â© 2016 IEEE.', '', '', 'Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc.', 'NA', '9781509006113', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Educational data classification using selective NaÃ¯ve Bayes for quota categorization', 'Proceedings of the 2014 IEEE International Conference on MOOCs, Innovation and Technology in Education, IEEE MITE 2014 ', '2015', '', '118-121', '10.1109/MITE.2014.7020253', '', 'Deptt. of Computer Engineering, Mewar University, Chittorgarh, Rajasthan, India; Department of Computer Engineering, Manipal University Jaipur, District Bagaru, Jaipur, Rajasthan, India', 'Education data classification is a growing interest in the research of data mining. Correctly identifying the education data into particular category is still presenting challenge because of large and vast amount of features in the dataset. In regards to the existing classifying approaches, NaÃ¯ve Bayes is potentially good at serving as a classification model due to its simplicity and accuracy. Naive Bayes is one of the most efficient and effective algorithms for data mining. The aim of this paper is to highlight the performance of employing NaÃ¯ve Bayes in education data classification. The data extracted could be used to Find Meaningful Pattern for the students on the real time problem scenario application to be monitored at college level. Also the model can be used for the future planning of student selection criteria at college level. Â© 2014 IEEE.', '', '', 'Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc.', 'NA', '9781479968763', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Effect of ambient temperature rise on the LED life time resource', 'Light and Engineering ', '2016', '24', '56-60', '746128060NA', '', 'Department of Electrical Engineering, Suresh Gyan Vihar University, Jaipur, India; Department of Electrical and Electronics Engineering, Manipal University, Jaipur, India', 'The impact of ambient temperature rise and, therefore T-point temperature rise too, on the life time of LEDs is analysed in this paper. From the research conducted so far it is understood that life time resource of LEDs is mainly dependent on junction temperature. For most of the high power LEDs, which are enclosed inside a luminaire, dissipation of junction heat from the device is a major concern for most of the manufacturers. In this paper, an attempt has been made to investigate the underlying constraints of heat dissipation and subsequently using LEDs as a general light source. The investigation is carried out in two steps. Firstly, the degradation in light output with corresponding increase in ambient temperature is explored. Secondly, the impact of increase in T-point temperature on the lifetime of the LEDs is observed. The experiment is conducted using high power LEDs and the same is subjected to external thermal stress. The temperature inside the environmental chamber represents the ambient temperature for the LED and thus by gradually increasing the ambient temperature the T-point temperature is also increased. The temperature of the chamber and the T-point are measured by using k-type thermocouple. The corresponding data hence obtained are tabulated and correlated with light output. The results are analysed using statistical tool to obtain the relation between the parameters. Â© 2016, LLC Editorial of Journal â€œLight Technikâ€. All rights reserved.', '', '', 'LLC Editorial of Journal \"Light Technik\"', '02362945', 'NA', '', '', 'Journal', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Effect of annealing on sol-gel derived TiO2 nanoparticles in acidic medium', '2017 International Conference On Nextgen Electronic Technologies: Silicon to Software, ICNETS2 2017 ', '2017', '', '105-107', '10.1109/ICNETS2.2017.8067908', '', 'Department of Physics, Manipal University Jaipur, Jaipur, Rajasthan, India', 'TiO2 nanoparticles are prepared by sol-gel method. As revealed by X-ray diffraction (XRD) spectra the nanoparticles change their phase from anatase to rutile when the annealing temperature goes beyond 650Â°C. W-H plot for the powder samples annealed at 450Â°C and 750Â°C shows the presence of tensile strain in them which affects the particle size. The difference in particle sizes obtained from Debye-Scherer formula and W-H plot is seen to reduce for lesser strain value. The field emission scanning electron microscope (FESEM) images are observed to depict the agglomerated clusters of the particles whose average size favors the XRD results. The absorption is seen to show a red shift, as annealing temperature is raised. Â© 2017 IEEE.', '', '', 'Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc.', 'NA', '9781509059126', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Effect of annealing on the structural and optical properties of TiO2 powder prepared by sol-gel route', 'AIP Conference Proceedings ', '2016', '1728', '', '10.1063/1.4946437', '', 'Department of Physics, Manipal University Jaipur, Jaipur Rajasthan, India', 'Using titanium isopropoxide as the precursor, Titanium dioxide (TiO2) powder was synthesized via sol-gel method, a promising low temperature route for preparing nanosized metal oxide semiconductors with good homogeneity at low cost. The as-prepared nano powder was thermally treated in air at 550, 650, 750, 900 and 1100Â°C for 1hr after drying at room temperature and used for further characterization. X-ray diffraction measurements showed that the annealing treatment has a strong impact on the crystal phase of TiO2 samples. The crystallite size as calculated from Debye Scherer formula lies in the range 29-69?nm and is found to increase with increase in annealing temperature. Photoluminescence studies exhibit an improvement in the optical efficiency of the samples with post synthesis heat treatment. Annealing at temperature above 900Â°C results in a degradation of the structural and optical quality of the TiO2 nano powder samples. Â© 2016 Author(s).', '', '', 'American Institute of Physics Inc.', '0094243X', '9780735413757', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Effect of Current Variation on Carbon Black to synthesize MWCNTs using pulsed arc Discharge method', 'Materials Today: Proceedings ', '2017', '4', '9394-9398', '10.1016/j.matpr.2017.06.192', '', 'Department of Mechanical Engineering, Birla Institute of Technology and Science, Pilani, India; School of Automobile, Mechanical and Mechatronics, Manipal University, Jaipur, India', 'In this paper, we have studied the effect of various arc current on synthesis of carbon nanotubes (CNTs) using carbon black as a raw material by pulsed arc discharge technique which has not been reported in literature. We have traced the phase transformation of Carbon Black for various arc current from 22 to 40A at a constant time interval of 60sec in argon atmosphere. The phase transformation morphology was evaluated using X-ray Diffraction (XRD) and the Field emission scanning electron micrographs (FESEM) images shows the transformation of Carbon black to various structures and finally to tubular like structure through TEM (Transmission Electron Microscope) conform the MWCNTs formation. Â© 2017 Elsevier Ltd.', '', '', 'Elsevier Ltd', '22147853', 'NA', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Effect of curvature on the structural and magnetic properties of Ni film deposited on self-Assembled nanospheres', 'AIP Conference Proceedings ', '2016', '1728', '', '10.1063/1.4946414', '', 'Dept. of Physics, Manipal University Jaipur, Jaipur, India; UGC-DAE Consortium for Scientific Research, Indore, India; Dept. of Physics, ISLE, IPS Academy, Indore, India', 'Important experimental findings and their impact on physical properties of Ni thin film are presented with the focus on structural and magnetic property investigations. For this purpose, Ni film (40?nm) was deposited on polystyrene nanospheres (PS, diameter 800?nm) using electron beam evaporation technique simultaneously with a similar reference film on plane Si substrate. The structural properties of the films measured using XRD technique show nanocrystalline growth of Ni on both size PS spheres with an average grain size of âˆ¼ 78?nm, while high crystallinity was observed in the film deposited onto plane Si substrate. A lower coercivity (9 mT) was observed in the Ni/(800?nm) PS as compared to the film deposited on 530?nm PS (23 mT) (our earlier study) and Ni/Si (20 mT). The observed changes in structural and magnetic properties are attributed to the curvature induced modifications at atomic level. Â© 2016 Author(s).', '', '', 'American Institute of Physics Inc.', '0094243X', '9780735413757', '', '', 'Conference Paper', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', ''),
('', 'Effect of different metal catalysts on the growth of Carbon Nanotubes by chemical vapor deposition using five step process', 'Journal of Optoelectronics and Advanced Materials ', '2015', '17', '1728-1733', '311033722NA', '', 'Department of ECE, MNIT, Jaipur, India; ECE, Manipal University Jaipur, India', 'Carbon nanotubes are synthesized by using chemical vapor deposition method in which Iron, Nickel and Cobalt are used as catalyst. By chemical vapor deposition decomposition of acetylene is achieved at 850Â°C and the carbon was deposited on different substrates (Glass and Silicon) in the presence of catalyst for the carbon nanotube growth. The effect of different metal catalysts on the growth of the carbon nanotubes is studied by the experiment performed. The carbon nanotubes synthesized by different catalysts on different substrates are characterized using Scanning electron microscopy (SEM), Xray diffraction (XRD) techniques and transmission electron microscopy (TEM). The experimental work for the synthesis of CNTs is performed at MRC, MNIT Jaipur. In this paper, the synthesis of carbon nanotubes is reported and also their fabrication and characterization. The reported procedure for the synthesis of carbon nanotubes is a five step process for CVD in order to obtain a high yield and purity.', '', '', 'National Institute of Optoelectronics', '14544164', 'NA', '', '', 'Journal', '', 'SCOPUS', '', '', '', '');
